The concept of ''machishū'' is a continuation of earlier urban groups such as the {{ill|Kyowarawa|ja|京童}} of the {{ill|Heian period|ja|平安時代}} and later evolved into the {{ill|Chōnin|ja|町人}} class during the early modern {{ill|Edo period|ja|江戸時代}}.
Today, it is commonly pronounced as "machishū," but contemporary historical sources such as the {{ill|Setsuyōshū|ja|節要集}} and the {{ill|Nippo Jisho|ja|日葡辞書}} suggest that it was pronounced as "chōshū."== See Also == * [[:en:Hokke-ikki|Hokke-ikki]] * {{ill|Kan'ei culture|ja|寛永文化}} * {{ill|Machikōji|ja|町小路}}
